sentences: Robert Barry (December 4, 1932 - January 8, 2018) was an American jazz musician.
He was a percussionist who played with Miles Davis, Gene Ammons, Fred Anderson and Johnny Griffin but was best known for his work with Sun Ra and  The Sun Ra Arkestra.
He joined the Sun Ra Arkestra in the 1950s appearing on albums such as We Travel the Space Ways, Nubians of Plutonia, and Sun Song
